  <bioghist id="aspace_2eef4d1300b6215237443efbd02c7010">
    <head>ORGANIZATIONAL HISTORY</head>
<p>C. R. Henderson, for many years a professor in the Department of Animal Science, was world-renowned in the area of animal breeding.</p>  </bioghist>
  <scopecontent id="aspace_f62558a5628e775ac83f924c08db1acf">
    <head>COLLECTION DESCRIPTION</head>
<p>Records pertaining to research and extension, including the New York State Fair, particularly with sheep, swine, and goats, 1949-1973.</p><p> Also, two video cassettes of "The Legacy of C. R. Henderson," from the American Dairy Science Association Symposium, June 1990, and radio talks (1949-1955) given by faculty over the Rural Radio Network.</p>  </scopecontent>
  <prefercite id="aspace_2b2051ef1738685d90df4f56f050014a">
    <head>Cite As:</head>
<p>Department of Animal Science records, #21-14-2565. Division of Rare and Manuscript Collections, Cornell University Library.</p>  </prefercite>
